etymology.description: 女(女) (nǚ, "woman") + 那(那) (nà, "that") = semantic element indicating femininity + phonetic element providing pronunciation -> used as a feminine name component/
etymology.interpretation: 娜(娜) (nà, "a name") combines 女(女) to indicate a female name or noun, and phonetic 那(那) to provide the pronunciation.

examples.chinese: 娜在校园中努力学习(娜在校園中努力學習)。
examples.pinyin: Nà zài xiàoyuán zhōng nǔlì xuéxí。
